snippet.textDisplay:
@Marco Reviews It's capitalism that's creates waste, because capitalists do whatever it takes to turn a profit, even at the cost to the environment. For example, in the olden days, if your shoe was in disrepair, you could take it to the cobblers to help repair your shoe, thus minimizing waste to the environment. However, capitalism has made the production of shoes so cheap, so much that most shoe owners would rather throw away a repairable shoe and buy a new shoe, at the expense to the environment. This is how capitalism shapes society into a throwaway society, and is destroying the planet in the process.

In my example I used shoes, but you can replace shoes with almost any other example. If your earphones stop working, instead taking it to a repair shop, most people just throw it away and buy a new pair of earphones. Because capitalism makes it such that it's cheaper to just go and buy a new product (at expense to the environment) rather than try to fix a broken but repairable product.
